# Git & PR Workflow

Read [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) and [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) for full detail.

## Branches

`feature/<short-kebab-description>` — for example `feature/v1-static-site`.

## Commits

Conventional Commits, GPG-signed when committing locally:

```text
type(scope): imperative summary
```

Examples:

- `feat(blog): migrate Ghost archive to content collection`
- `feat(projects): add GPXplore case study`
- `fix(seo): omit analytics script when token is absent`
- `docs(spec): add RSS feed spec`

## PRs

- Title: conventional commit style for the main outcome.
- Body: `## Summary` bullets + `## Test plan` checkboxes.
- Verification: `npm test` and `npm run build` once the project exists.

## Spec-Driven Work

Check `specs/`, `specs/backlog--ongoing.md`, and `CONTEXT.md` before feature work. Move shipped specs to `specs/built/` and update `specs/spec-status--ongoing.md`.

Do not create commits or PRs unless the user explicitly asks.

